==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*snutra-'', perhaps from the same Indo-European root as Greek [[νοος]] ‘mind’.  Cognate with Old High German [[snottar]], Old Norse [[snotr]], Gothic [[𐍃𐌽𐌿𐍄𐍂𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'snotor/

===Adjective===
'''snotor'''
# [[wise]], [[clever]]

